19/09/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia --Parliament convened a special session Thursday (18 September) on the security situation in Macedonia, in light of recent police and army operations against the group calling itself the Albanian National Army. 
The main opposition presented a report on the security situation in the last eleven months and appealed to the coalition cabinet to guarantee security and stability throughout the country. 
All parliamentarians conceded there should be political, national and interethnic unity against violence and extremism.
Also on Thursday, Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski met with Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski, Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski, Army Chief of Staff General Metodi Stamboliski and Deputy Interior Minister Hazbi Lika. 
The officials discussed defence and security reforms, including the creation of a special counterterrorism unit within the Macedonian Army. 
(MIA, A1 TV, Makfax - 18/09/03)
